# ⚡ EV Dynamic Charging Simulator — Walkthrough

## Overview

I read your **literature review** on EV dynamic charging characteristics and built a **fully interactive, physics-based simulator** that brings the research to life. The simulator covers all the key topics from your reviewed papers.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **To run:** Open [index.html](file:///Users/overwatch/Documents/Dynamic%20Charging/index.html) in a browser, or serve locally with `python3 -m http.server 8080` from the project directory and visit `http://localhost:8080`

---

## 📚 What I Read from Your Literature Review

From your research materials, I extracted these core concepts to simulate:

| Topic | Source | Key Concept |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| **CC-CV Charging** | 5 papers (IEEE TPEL, TIE, TTE) | Constant Current → Constant Voltage transition at ~80% SoC |
| **Converter Topologies** | LLC, LCL, LCC resonant | Each topology has different efficiency (95–98.8%) and harmonic profiles |
| **Grid Harmonics** | IEEE 519-2022 | Non-linear loads inject harmonics; THD limit = 5% at PCC |
| **Multi-EV Impact** | Multiple papers | Aggregate load is complex, time-varying; 40.8% peak reduction possible |
| **Thermal-Adaptive** | MSCC-CV-CT paper | Dynamic CC-CV profiles, not static |

---

## 🎯 Simulator Features

### 1. CC-CV Charging Profile Simulation

The core simulation models a **realistic Li-ion battery** with:
- **Open-circuit voltage (OCV) curve** — polynomial fit to real Li-ion characteristics
- **Internal resistance model** — varies with SoC (higher at low/high SoC)
- **CC mode**: Fixed current, rising voltage, SoC ~10-80%
- **CV mode**: Capped voltage, exponentially decaying current, SoC ~80-100%

