## 🏗️ Technical Architecture

### Files Created

| File | Purpose | Lines |
|------|---------|-------|
| [index.html](file:///Users/overwatch/Documents/Dynamic%20Charging/index.html) | Page structure — all sections | ~300 |
| [styles.css](file:///Users/overwatch/Documents/Dynamic%20Charging/styles.css) | Dark theme, glassmorphism, responsive layout | ~700 |
| [simulation.js](file:///Users/overwatch/Documents/Dynamic%20Charging/simulation.js) | Physics engine, chart rendering, simulation loop | ~700 |

### Physics Model

The battery model uses these equations derived from the literature:

```
OCV(SoC) = V_min + (V_max - V_min) × (0.05 + 0.75s + 0.35s² - 0.15s³)

R_int(SoC) = R_base × (1.5 - 0.8s + 0.6s²)

CC Mode: I = I_max,  V = OCV + I×R_int,  P = V×I
CV Mode: V = V_max,  I = I_max × e^(-3.5 × progress),  P = V×I

THD = √(Σ I_h²) / I_1 × 100%
PF = 0.99 / √(1 + (THD/100)²)
```

### Key Design Decisions

- **Zero dependencies** — Pure HTML/CSS/JS, no external chart libraries
- **Custom canvas charts** — High-performance rendering with glow effects
- **Physics-based** — Not mockup data; actual differential equation integration
- **Literature-derived** — All harmonic profiles and efficiency values come from the reviewed papers

